**Panic on serialization failure**: Every tool handler uses `.expect("serialize")` on `facet_json::to_string_pretty`. If a value contains data that cannot be serialized (e.g., non-UTF-8 strings from git, unusual edge cases in facet-json), this panics and kills the MCP server process. Since these are tool handlers invoked over a protocol transport, a panic means the client gets a broken pipe with no error message. These should propagate errors or return an error string, consistent with how other errors are handled in the same functions.